nodes.body:
Here are the [benchmark results](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/run-detail/2a7260ed-b754-457b-b690-ef798cad6016) for commit 2062f3d318d7438d3531b0cecbb65acf14b59b4d.
There were [no significant changes](http://speed.lean-fro.org/mathlib4/compare/65e9db48-42b5-49fc-bd3b-e378bcde0b12/to/2a7260ed-b754-457b-b690-ef798cad6016) against commit cad0ed8b1a312ec32b9ae2e97705738fa5dc3199.

I've written a bash script and a Magma program to extract all files whose instruction count differs by at least 10⁹, and it reports this:
```text
==============================================================================
General information:
  build:                                              +1.1833 * 10⁹ 
(+0.00101%)

Files that got slower:
  Mathlib.Analysis.NormedSpace.PiTensorProduct.InjectiveSeminorm:
                                                      +1.4072 * 10⁹ (+0.504%)

Files that got faster:
==============================================================================
```
...even though this file is not even touched by the PR!?

Pull request successfully merged into master.

I scrolled through it all. Great!
